,"position":{"start":{"line":54,"column":1},"end":{"line":54,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Raster Calculator","position":{"start":{"line":54,"column":1},"end":{"line":54,"column":1}},"key":"FEXIAsJZOQ"}],"identifier":"raster-calculator","label":"Raster Calculator","html_id":"raster-calculator","implicit":true,"key":"i30hbRoKd7"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":56,"column":1},"end":{"line":56,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"The Cell Statistics tool has a limited number of mathematical operations. The ","position":{"start":{"line":56,"column":1},"end":{"line":56,"column":1}},"key":"ebl8vtnFrQ"},{"type":"link","url":"https://pro.arcgis.com/en/pro-app/3.3/tool-reference/spatial-analyst/raster-calculator.htm","position":{"start":{"line":56,"column":1},"end":{"line":56,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Raster Calculator tool","position":{"start":{"line":56,"column":1},"end":{"line":56,"column":1}},"key":"P6i1cyuDv3"}],"urlSource":"https://pro.arcgis.com/en/pro-app/3.3/tool-reference/spatial-analyst/raster-calculator.htm","key":"pdXChu99kZ"},{"type":"text","value":" in ArcGIS Pro or QGIS under ","position":{"start":{"line":56,"column":1},"end":{"line":56,"column":1}},"key":"yli7gqgdnL"},{"type":"link","url":"https://docs.qgis.org/3.44/en/docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/rasteranalysis.html","position":{"start":{"line":56,"column":1},"end":{"line":56,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Raster analysis","position":{"start":{"line":56,"column":1},"end":{"line":56,"column":1}},"key":"UBuWTWx9Nj"}],"urlSource":"https://docs.qgis.org/3.44/en/docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/rasteranalysis.html","key":"TrNmQXtn0E"},{"type":"text","value":" provides more flexibility in defining such operations.","position":{"start":{"line":56,"column":1},"end":{"line":56,"column":1}},"key":"Rz1VBiZg64"}],"key":"vptLObKiQy"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":58,"column":1},"end":{"line":58,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"To illustrate, we can combine the following raster layers. The first layer represents architecture with values ranging from 1 to 13 over a background of 0:","position":{"start":{"line":58,"column":1},"end":{"line":58,"column":1}},"key":"RRkRXFLeQ5"}],"key":"KmO6d3mPGk"},{"type":"image","url":"/rcinput1-679d88a3d8246c3184ebaffa3e802dca.jpg","alt":"Raster Calculator","width":"80%","align":"center","class":"bg-primary mb-1","key":"NhNvZDpn1X","urlSource":"/images/rcinput1.jpg"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":67,"column":1},"end":{"line":67,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"The second layer represents a road with a value of 14 over a background of 0:","position":{"start":{"line":67,"column":1},"end":{"line":67,"column":1}},"key":"XEDQNWW8id"}],"key":"TIbgf2j5I6"},{"type":"image","url":"/rcinput2-3e7c2bca861e46401607d48505a891fc.jpg","alt":"Raster Calculator","width":"80%","align":"center","class":"bg-primary mb-1","key":"nqE2YyJ7le","urlSource":"/images/rcinput2.jpg"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":76,"column":1},"end":{"line":76,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"We could run the Cell Statistics tool with the statistic set to sum, or we could run Raster Calculator with the following formula, adding these two layers together:","position":{"start":{"line":76,"column":1},"end":{"line":76,"column":1}},"key":"EhZh4QEn27"}],"key":"kUIUYmUz7j"},{"type":"image","url":"/rc-2a8b381f0ba602d75fbdd6293d4e4091.jpg","alt":"Raster Calculator","width":"50%","align":"center","class":"bg-primary mb-1","key":"cy6Pp5fwB3","urlSource":"/images/rc.jpg"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":85,"column":1},"end":{"line":85,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Doing so, we generate an output where 0 still represents the background, 1 to 13 still represent mounds, 14 still represents the road, but we now have additional values 15 and 27 that represent areas where the road overlaps architecture. In the case of 15, we have areas where the road overlaps the architecture with the value of 1, and in the case of 27, we have areas where the road overlaps the architecture with a value of 13:","position":{"start":{"line":85,"column":1},"end":{"line":85,"column":1}},"key":"bOQQx0o99O"}],"key":"rb0n1En3r5"},{"type":"image","url":"/rcoutput-1f32d695376479d7d613a8cdfb1054c3.jpg","alt":"Raster Calculator","width":"80%","align":"center","class":"bg-primary mb-1","key":"UlAFFTSZgw","urlSource":"/images/rcoutput.jpg"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":94,"column":1},"end":{"line":94,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"We can also set Boolean operations, or true/false operations. If we run the following operation on the above output:","position":{"start":{"line":94,"column":1},"end":{"line":94,"column":1}},"key":"jjHbZlODoo"}],"key":"ntL874ietV"},{"type":"code","lang":"","value":"\"input.tif\"  <= 14","position":{"start":{"line":96,"column":1},"end":{"line":98,"column":1}},"key":"nyu74Mjr4F"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":100,"column":1},"end":{"line":100,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"We get an image where values less than or equal to 14 have been set 1, and values above 14 have been set to 0, separating areas where the road crosses architecture:","position":{"start":{"line":100,"column":1},"end":{"line":100,"column":1}},"key":"mSoIx97W9P"}],"key":"Y78FYhy7QK"},{"type":"image","url":"/rcoutput2-7901704eaacaa2d0e1998c0400023da5.jpg","alt":"Raster Calculator","width":"80%","align":"center","class":"bg-primary mb-1","key":"tmZF2ZEI62","urlSource":"/images/rcoutput2.jpg"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":109,"column":1},"end":{"line":109,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"We can also set conditional statements. The following operation defines a conditional statement that where values in the DEM are less than 300, they should be set to 0, otherwise all other values should keep the same value in the raster. In ArcGIS Pro’s Raster Calculator, run the following:","position":{"start":{"line":109,"column":1},"end":{"line":109,"column":1}},"key":"tT4vJj7aom"}],"key":"IHcNQGi1SM"},{"type":"code","lang":"","value":"Con(\"dem.tif\" < 300, 0, \"dem.tif\")","position":{"start":{"line":111,"column":1},"end":{"line":113,"column":1}},"key":"stdyUIhQN3"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":115,"column":1},"end":{"line":115,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"In QGIS, use if( instead of Con(","position":{"start":{"line":115,"column":1},"end":{"line":115,"column":1}},"key":"qFEcFdHFxY"}],"key":"kyzVwsmXod"},{"type":"code","lang":"","value":"if(\"dem.tif\" < 300, 0, \"dem.tif\") ","position":{"start":{"line":117,"column":1},"end":{"line":119,"column":1}},"key":"zkC1IfEDQ9"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":121,"column":1},"end":{"line":121,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"When applied to the following DEM:","position":{"start":{"line":121,"column":1},"end":{"line":121,"column":1}},"key":"esjdTQPs1b"}],"key":"vp8e3vuoV7"},{"type":"image","url":"/demcon1-19f8261033b9b5aeb85f2a73ad1981a2.jpg","alt":"Conditional","width":"80%","align":"center","class":"bg-primary mb-1","key":"rk3ePc1Igg","urlSource":"/images/demcon1.jpg"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":130,"column":1},"end":{"line":130,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"We get the following output:","position":{"start":{"line":130,"column":1},"end":{"line":130,"column":1}},"key":"OdzqTHf6I7"}],"key":"UT4dUhJhFl"},{"type":"image","url":"/demcon2-4f1c522d920ad244dad16545e629b67a.jpg","alt":"Conditional","width":"80%","align":"center","class":"bg-primary mb-1","key":"uY7vpExgrX","urlSource":"/images/demcon2.jpg"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":139,"column":1},"end":{"line":139,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"We can also use a conditional statement to replace NoData values with values from another raster. In the following example, we are filling the voids of a 1-arc second SRTM DEM with the values from a void-filled 3-arc second SRTM DEM. If we set the cell size under Environments to Minimum of Inputs, the output raster will be resampled to 1-arc second resolution.","position":{"start":{"line":139,"column":1},"end":{"line":139,"column":1}},"key":"DcMhIr8Avj"}],"key":"p9B5OXWzVL"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":141,"column":1},"end":{"line":141,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"In ArcGIS Pro:","position":{"start":{"line":141,"column":1},"end":{"line":141,"column":1}},"key":"tTtrOsevXv"}],"key":"MxaHHw6VNe"},{"type":"code","lang":"","value":"Con(IsNull(\"1arc_dem.tif\") , \"3arc_dem.tif\", \"1arc_dem.tif\")","position":{"start":{"line":143,"column":1},"end":{"line":145,"column":1}},"key":"JdmxlA17Ge"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":147,"column":1},"end":{"line":147,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"In QGIS, you first need to run the Fill NoData cells tool under ","position":{"start":{"line":147,"column":1},"end":{"line":147,"column":1}},"key":"xQ05gHK3Ko"},{"type":"link","url":"https://docs.qgis.org/3.44/en/docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/rastertools.html","position":{"start":{"line":147,"column":1},"end":{"line":147,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Raster tools","position":{"start":{"line":147,"column":1},"end":{"line":147,"column":1}},"key":"hRTH0uEhvm"}],"urlSource":"https://docs.qgis.org/3.44/en/docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/rastertools.html","key":"nnZgjJfth0"},{"type":"text","value":" to define a NoData value, for example, -9999. Then in Raster Calculator copy the following expression:","position":{"start":{"line":147,"column":1},"end":{"line":147,"column":1}},"key":"FLDs2MxNUY"}],"key":"pnujC89Ke0"},{"type":"code","lang":"","value":"if(\"1arc_dem.tif\" = -9999, \"3arc_dem.tif\", \"1arc_dem.tif\")","position":{"start":{"line":149,"column":1},"end":{"line":151,"column":1}},"key":"jhvbMibvsc"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":153,"column":1},"end":{"line":153,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Stated in plain English, this conditional statement can be read as “When the 1-arc second DEM has NoData, replace these values with those from the 3-arc second DEM, otherwise keep the 1-arc second DEM.”","position":{"start":{"line":153,"column":1},"end":{"line":153,"column":1}},"key":"bJRjnejDpG"}],"key":"znEF1NoZyz"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":155,"column":1},"end":{"line":155,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"The following raster layer represents the 1-arc second SRTM DEM with voids:","position":{"start":{"line":155,"column":1},"end":{"line":155,"column":1}},"key":"R0sZEQKxXx"}],"key":"FNr2MEGcn5"},{"type":"image","url":"/conditional-e32507a18f795f7805bdfb955665252e.jpg","alt":"Conditional","width":"80%","align":"center","class":"bg-primary mb-1","key":"zEQMXS2IjP","urlSource":"/images/conditional.jpg"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":164,"column":1},"end":{"line":164,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"And the result of the raster calculator operation:","position":{"start":{"line":164,"column":1},"end":{"line":164,"column":1}},"key":"StyWljL7JX"}],"key":"TU1d8pwKFv"},{"type":"image","url":"/conditional2-8918e047cb30778a9588356fc574e8f1.jpg","alt":"Conditional","width":"80%","align":"center","class":"bg-primary mb-1","key":"FzWEeQ29Tr","urlSource":"/images/conditional2.jpg"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":173,"column":1},"end":{"line":173,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Note that QGIS has several Raster Calculator tools that run the same processes but use different syntax. If running Raster Calculator from Raster analysis, you must first load the input layers, then you can define an expression using these input layers and the appropriate operations. Another Raster Calculator tool is available under GDAL. Here, you can define any input rasters as A, B, C, D, E, or F. Then the expression can be defined using gdalnumeric syntax, for example, A-B will subtract the second raster from the first, and A*2 will multiple all values in the raster by a factor of 2. An additional Raster Calculator is available under Raster -> Raster Calculator, which does not require the inputs to be defined; instead, all rasters under Layers are available. (The latter is my preferred version of Raster Calculator in QGIS.)","position":{"start":{"line":173,"column":1},"end":{"line":173,"column":1}},"key":"R12aErojzR"}],"key":"madRgRJWti"}],"key":"s2BtPkmhSz"}],"key":"PULpPfnCfM"},"references":{"cite":{"order":[],"data":{}}}}